================================================================================
KEY ARCHITECTURAL DECISIONS (Documented for Reference)
================================================================================

1. SUPABASE = Primary Database
   - Free tier: 500MB, 50K MAU, PostGIS, RLS, auto-REST API
   - Self-host option available for Kenyan data sovereignty
   - NOT a replacement for MongoDB, Redis, or Mosquitto

2. MONGODB = Time-Series Telemetry (Keep)
   - Purpose-built for high-write sensor data
   - Built-in data expiration and aggregation pipeline
   - MongoDB Atlas free tier (512MB) available if needed

3. MOSQUITTO MQTT = Real-Time Pub/Sub (Keep)
   - Low bandwidth (critical on Safaricom 3G)
   - QoS guarantees (0/1/2) -- Supabase Realtime has none
   - Topic-level ACL security
   - Industry standard for IoT/telemetry

4. REDIS = Caching (Optional for MVP)
   - Identity service uses it for token caching
   - Graceful degradation if unavailable
   - Add when scaling beyond single server

5. DATABASE_MODE = supabase (default) | local (offline dev)
   - Services read DATABASE_MODE to choose connection target
   - Docker PostgreSQL only starts with `--profile local-db`

